oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Duke of Paducah interview - Biff Collie - 1965-03-16
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Recording of an interview with the Duke of Paducah (comedian/performer), conducted by Biff Collie on March 16, 1965.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Biff Collie introduces the Duke of Paducah -- Duke of Paducah says his real name, his nickname, and says his catch phrase -- Duke of Paducah talks about when he started his career in radio with his Dixieland jazz band -- Duke of Paducah talks about where he got his name, in St. Louis -- Duke of Paducah talks about playing rodeos and being inducted into the Western Hall of Fame -- Duke of Paducah talks about his work in the musical theatre -- Duke of Paducah talks about it taking a long time to learn how to be funny -- Duke of Paducah talks about Joe Miller, the comedian -- Duke of Paducah talk about being sincere with his comedy -- Duke of Paducah talks about how he comes up with his material -- Duke of Paducah talks about repeated old material -- Duke of Paducah talks about Jamup & Honey -- Duke of Paducah talks about writing out material -- Duke of Paducah talks about subject matter in his material -- Duke of Paducah talks about always having confidence during his shows -- Duke of Paducah talks about being controlling of his audiences -- Duke of Paducah talks about hecklers -- Collie concludes the interview
